# Making a new page

This is a bit complicated so hang on. To create a new page, first go to the page where you want it to be linked. For example, if you want to add a community to the 'communities' page, go there. Then edit the page and create a new entry. Save your changes.

Now your new entry should show up like this:

 <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/usvdh/hku.one.photos/refs/heads/main/makingnewpage.png" alt="example" width="200" style="border: 5px solid #000;" /> 

Click on the question mark and you will be taken to the page creation page. Because we are adding a page for a new community, we want it to end up in the 'communities' folder:

 <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/usvdh/hku.one.photos/refs/heads/main/makingnewpage2.png" alt="example" width="300" style="border: 5px solid #000;" /> 

Then edit the page as usual. See [[ikiwiki/formatting/]] for formatting help. 

